Top Stories (March 9)

CALIFORNIA UTILITIES COMMISSION SAYS STATE CAN RAISE RATES TO PAY FOR POWER
Utility regulators Wednesday acknowledged that all the money the state is 
spending on power can be passed along in electric rates -- either by wrapping 
it into existing charges or by boosting people's electric bills.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/09/krtbn/0000-0372-SA-ELECTRIC-RATES

POWER WHOLESALERS MUST REFUND $69M
Federal regulators Friday ordered power wholesalers to refund $69 million in 
excessive charges to California utilities, hundreds of millions less than 
state officials sought.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/03/09/ao/0000-5971-power-woes

FEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSION OK'S AES BUY OF IPALCO
The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission approved AES Corp.'s acquisition of 
Ipalco Enterprises Inc. in a stock-for-stock transaction announced last July.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/09/eng-djn/eng-djn_150404_208_838210392278

AES NEW ENERGY BECOMES 15TH TEXAS RETAIL ELECTRIC PROVIDER
An application from AES New Energy Inc. to sell electricity when the state 
opens its power market to competition Jan. 1 has been approved by the Texas 
Public Utility Commission.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/09/eng-djn/eng-djn_210050_48_9884398807772

TWO FLORIDA ELECTRIC UTILITIES TO INCREASE RATES
The Florida Public Service Commission on Tuesday approved requests of Tampa 
Electric Co. and Florida Power Corp. to increase bills slightly to compensate 
for rising costs of natural gas, oil and coal.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/09/krtbn/0000-0469-TM-ELECTRIC

NEW U.S.-MEXICO POWER TRANSMISSION LINK APPROVED: ABRAHAM
U.S. Energy Secretary Spencer Abraham, speaking in Mexico City on his maiden 
foreign trip in the post, said the United States has approved a new electric 
power transmission line connecting Brownsville, Texas, and the city of 
Matamoros, in northern Mexico, according to a report in Mexican financial 
daily El Economista.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/imexnews
/2001/03/09/eng-imenews/eng-imenews_134025_141_820200146176

